## 6. Human oversight _(DSK OH KI-Systeme 2025-06)_

{% if model.is_high_risk %}
### ⚖️ Obligation for high-risk AI — to be fulfilled / evidenced by the deployer (Art. 14 EU AI Act)

1. **Four-eyes principle** before every final decision with legal effect.
   A qualified natural person must review the AI result and be able to
   override it (document the override capability).
2. **Escalation path** for critical or unclear outputs — designated
   contact person, escalation time (e.g. max. 24h), escalation protocol.
3. **Override logs** — every deviation of the final decision from the AI suggestion
   must be logged with a justification (linked to the audit trail, Art. 12 AI Act).
4. **Duty to inform** data subjects — persons subject to AI processing
   must be explicitly informed (Art. 50 EU AI Act + Art. 13–14 GDPR).
5. **Training of the reviewing persons** — qualified oversight requires an
   understanding of both how the AI works and of the domain (Art. 4 AI Act).
{% else %}
**Recommended even for limited risk:**

- Review results before use; no automated decisions without
  human oversight.
- Document the escalation path for critical outputs.
- Inform users about the use of AI (Art. 50 EU AI Act).
{% endif %}

